        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-12-07 14:32:29.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI'm not sure to understand why we need this start-kafka.sh script to be persisted. At the moment, without this patch, when I go in the kafka container, \n\nbash-4.3# which start-kafka.sh\n/usr/bin/start-kafka.sh\n\nso it's already picking the right one. So I tend to think it is useless to mount the script, and fork it.\n\nIs there any particular reason we're doing this?",
        "patchset_number": 1
